name: Volksfest with Eddie Korosa
description: On Sunday, July 2nd the Peoria German-American Society will be hosting their annual Volksfest at Hickory Grove Park from noon to 8 pm - Free Admission and Parking. This is a family friendly event.Hickory Grove Park, 12403 Hickory Grove Rd., Dunlap is just north of Peoria. Take Route 40 North to Hickory Grove Rd. Entertainment Lineup includes: Eddie Korosa from Chicago, Al u2019s Pals, and Lindenhof Echoes.To recognize the importance of the Fourth of July, we will have an American flag raising with members of our club dressed in military attire from the 1800 u2019s at around 1pm. At around 2:30pm there will be a dance demonstration by area performers dressed in period attire from the Civil War era.Also, new this year is a Volkswagen Family of Car Cruis u2019n which includes Audi and Porche., which runs from noon to 5:00 pm. Entry is free. The driver or rider will receive a pass good for one beverage or sandwich if they arrive before 2pm.Other activities will include: German gift tent, nagelspielen, stein holding, soccer, 50/50 raffle, and a shooting tent. Air gun shooters have the opportunity to earn prizes. A Kinder Park is available for the kids. German food available including full dinners. Main food line will end around 6 pm. Sandwich and pretzel booth are open longer.German and domestic beer are available, along with soft drinks and a cash bar. No outside coolers are permitted. Only service animals are allowed. No ATM on site.

name: Joe Shadid: Live at the Museum
description: Join us this July for Joe Shadid: Live at the Museum. With music inspired by the Peoria Riverfront Museum's Collection of American Folk Art, enjoy the sounds of this accomplished musician in a live concert! Joe George Shadid is a songwriter, film composer, and video host of music YouTube channel, REVERB .Joe u2019s debut record, Beautiful Dreams, was signed to German indie label, Eternal Sound Records, in early 2019. The release was followed by a European tour. Joe supported this record on a solo tour in Japan later that year. Joe u2019s songs encompass a range of color, from folk and Americana, to cinematic and spacious. His tasteful use of string quartet on recordings adds a breath and emotion to his music.Joe u2019s work with REVERB has been featured in The New York Times, Consequence of Sound, Guitar Player Magazine, and People Magazine. And a number of the videos he has hosted/performed in have gone viral, earning him global notoriety amongst music and gear lovers.
